state

public static double[] state(double GM,
                             double a,
                             double e,
                             double i,
                             double Omega,
                             double omega,
                             double M0,
                             double dt)
Computes the satellite state vector from osculating Keplerian elements for elliptic orbits

Notes:
The semimajor axis a=Kep(0), dt and GM must be given in consistent units, e.g. [m], [s] and [m^3/s^2]. The resulting units of length and velocity are implied by the units of GM, e.g. [m] and [m/s].

Parameters:
GM - Gravitational coefficient (gravitational constant * mass of central body)
a - Semimajor axis
e - Eccentricity
i - Inclination [rad]
Omega - Longitude of the ascending node [rad] or is this RAAN? (I think it is RAAN)
omega - Argument of pericenter [rad]
M0 - Mean anomaly at epoch [rad]
dt - Time since epoch (seconds?)
Returns:
State vector (x,y,z,vx,vy,vz)
